title: Algorithmic Mutterings
text:
Hello! I’m Eitan Turok. I like building things. And I am an obsessive learner.
I am majoring in CS and Applied Mathematics at Columbia University. I am generally interested in deep learning (efficient training, geometric DL, interpretability) and theoretical CS (fine-grained complexity, graph algorithms).
I do research under Prof Itsik Pe’er predicting diseases from the microbiome with non-Eculdidean embeddings. I also do research under Prof Josh Alman on the fine-grained complexity of dynamic programming problems.
